# RAG Control Center - Comprehensive API Documentation

This document outlines the complete RESTful API architecture for the Dual-RAG backend. The backend is built using FastAPI and serves endpoints across five primary domains: **Auth**, **Users**, **Chat**, **Documents**, and **System & Logs**. 

All API routes (except the root health check) are prefixed with `/api/v1`.

---

## Authentication & Roles

The system uses Role-Based Access Control (RBAC). 
* **Standard Users:** Authenticate via Google OAuth. Tokens are standard JWTs passed in the `Authorization` header as a Bearer token.
* **Admin Users:** Authenticate via local credentials. The system generates a custom token (e.g., `admin-secret-token-<id>`) to bypass Google JWT validation for administrative actions.

**Header Format for Protected Routes:**
`Authorization: Bearer <Token>`

